text: Why, why WHY just ONCE can something like this be written in a way that isn't so embarrassingly cliched, downright predictable, straight up dumb, saccharine, insulting and willfully asking to be critiqued as "all white." It would be so refreshing to see Diane Keaton ONCE be cast as something other than a blundering, neurotic mess, Candice Bergen as something different than the "powerful sage," Mary Steenburgen as something other than the mouse who "pipes up!" every now and again, and for the love of Pete can Jane Fonda ever be anything other than the sassy, sex seeking missile? I'm not saying it has to be high brow, but couldn't it just aim to not be THIS predictable? And the men...Ha! As if any of the men cast in these roles would be dating women their own age! Yes of course there are some men who date women their own age, but Don Johnson's character wouldn't be one of them... And I'm not even saying that he'd be dating a 20 something because that isn't necessarily so, you can bet the woman would be in her 40's and at the most 50's, if he is supposed to be in his 70's. And wait a minute; why are the women in the show supposed to be in their 70's, but the men are only in their 60's? There's just no way, and so it sucks any hope of believability out of it. Wanting more is just naive on my part because there is undoubtedly a large audience who will expect nothing more from it and won't care or notice that it is the same drivel they've been handed a hundred times before. And MORE with the tired 50 shades "naughtiness?" A chance to advertise the franchise because probably the same studio. This is why I'm a moron for ever expecting more from Hollywood.
